# Add Free IPs to Dedicated Accounts

**Procedure to add additional IPs to an account**
If a client requested for new IPs to add their existing server, then please follow the procedure. We can only assign free IPs in same subnet customer currently have.

For example, if client server in subnet 64.235.48, then we can only assign IPs on that same subnet.  Follow the procedure to assign IPs.

**How to Find Free IPs**

- Login to Inventory
- Select ip range of new server in "Check IP usage:" in inventory.  its in the top in inventory

```diagram

```

- Then click on submit. You will see list of used and unused ips in this range. Unused IPs are labeled with BLUE and GREEN
- BLUE  - mean free IPs in the new platform. We can directly assign it to the customer account from the New Admin Panel. 

```diagram

```

- GREEN - mean free IPs in the old platform. Need to contact Mr Peter and move to the new platform. Only then we can assign to customer account. 

```diagram

```
